972	  \item The forgetful functor $\ModuleCat\,k \to \AddCommGrpCat$ recovers the iter-004 abelian-group cohomology (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_toModuleKSheaf_forgetCompare}), so the new $\HModule$ commutes with the existing $\Sheaf.\mathtt H$ on the underlying type level.
973	  \item Phase~A step~6 (Serre finiteness, $\finrank_k H^i(C, \mathcal F) < \infty$) remains the deep work to come, but is now expressible inside Mathlib's standard $\Module\,k$ API: the statement of Serre finiteness becomes a $\Module.\mathtt{Finite}\,k\,(\HModule\,k\,F\,n)$ predicate.
974	\end{itemize}
